# Any key listed here can also be supplied as a regular shell env var
# (e.g. `export FRED_API_KEY=...`). The process environment wins over this
# file — local.env is just a convenient single-machine fallback.
#
# To store this file outside the repo, set MARKET_HELPER_GDRIVE_ROOT in
# your shell profile (see below); the tools auto-load <ROOT>/local.env.
# If ROOT is unset or contains no local.env, tools fall back to this
# checked-in copy.
ALPHA_VANTAGE_API_KEY="your_alpha_vantage_api_key"
# FRED API key — register free at https://fred.stlouisfed.org/docs/api/api_key.html
# Required by `fred-macro-sync` (regime macro_nowcast layer). Missing key
# gracefully disables the macro layer instead of failing the whole regime run.
FRED_API_KEY="your_fred_api_key"
DEFAULT_PROD_ACCOUNT_ID="your_prod_account_id"
DEFAULT_DEV_ACCOUNT_ID="your_dev_or_paper_account_id"
IBKR_FLEX_QUERY_ID="your_ibkr_flex_query_id"
IBKR_FLEX_TOKEN="your_ibkr_flex_token"
# Optional: override the dashboard's default IBKR API host/port. Set per machine
# in your shell profile (NOT here, since this file is shared via GDrive). Defaults
# are 127.0.0.1:7497 (TWS paper). IB Gateway uses 4001 (live) / 4002 (paper).
# IBKR_PORT="4001"
# IBKR_HOST="127.0.0.1"
# Optional: artifact-mirror destination (e.g. a Google Drive sync folder).
# Set MARKET_HELPER_GDRIVE_ROOT in each machine's shell profile; the tools
# mirror reports into <ROOT>/Portfolio_Report/. The same ROOT also drives
# local.env discovery (see comment header above). Mirroring is silently
# skipped on hosts that don't set ROOT.
#
# Examples (set in your shell profile, not here, since paths differ per host):
#   macOS .zshrc:
#     export MARKET_HELPER_GDRIVE_ROOT="/Users/<you>/Library/CloudStorage/GoogleDrive-<email>/My Drive/005 Portfolio"
#   Windows PowerShell $PROFILE:
#     $env:MARKET_HELPER_GDRIVE_ROOT = "G:/My Drive/005 Portfolio"
#
# Optional: OpenClaw gateway for the AI+ trade-advisor tab (/advisor → AI+).
# The AI+ tab is opt-in and parallel to the always-on rule-based advisor. It
# reads OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN as the bearer token (process env wins, then this
# file). Leave it blank and the AI+ tab simply shows a "disabled" explainer; the
# rule-based surface is unaffected. Endpoint defaults to
# http://127.0.0.1:18789/v1 (override OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_URL); model defaults to
# openclaw/trade-advisor (override OPENCLAW_TRADE_ADVISOR_MODEL).
OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=
